caption: Everything I have tried at La Jolie Bleue is delicious. Their chocolate croissant is one of the best I have tried, and their chicken and kofta soufflés are amazing. You can feel the care the pastries were made with as you bite into them. And in the summer, their refreshers are awesome!
This is my favorite coffee shop in Georgetown. Everything is super fresh and delicious. The best latter and espresso ☕️ Customer care is superb! You feel home! Thank you 🥰

I crave the couscous and anticipate the weekend to come have it. All home baked pastries and savory dishes. We have yet to taste something we haven’t enjoyed. The family who owns La Jolie Bleue is so kind and friendly. We’re very glad they have opened shop here.
Literally the cutest little family owned bakery. Delicious cookies and they're so friendly, will be going again soon

Excellent pastries and service.  I didn't get the lady's name, but she was very accommodating for me and my friend when she noticed there wasn't a table available for us outside, she brought more chairs out so we could be comfortable. Very friendly and hospitable. Not to mention, the pastries are fantastic! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
This is the best place in DC to have morning coffee or lunch or any time that u want to enjoy some Mediterranean food Thank you for the service
(Translated by Google) it was good they don't have much  (Original) foi boa eles nao tem muita coisa

A gem of a place tucked in Georgetown! Excellent food. We tried the artichoke and spinach quiche, baklava, almond paste cookie and almond croissant. It was all fresh, delicious and authentic! Will definitely be recommending to friends and family and we will be back!
The chicken portabella quiche is the best quiche I've every had in my life!
The food is delicious and the owner is very kind !
Their chicken and kofta soufflés are absolutely delicious. I have not visited the cafe, but I do make sure to visit their stand every weekend at the Petworth Farmer’s Market.

This is a really terrific spot for some of DC's very best Mediterranean pastries and delicious, freshly made soups, quiches, spanakopita, merger sandwiches and, on weekends, couscous. There is a small dining space upstairs, but with a globally warmed Washington winter, it's usually more fun to sit outside and watch the buses go by. They make their own, really delicious croissants, but even better are the unique. North African style handmade pastries.  It's unpretentious, delicious, and affordable -- my favourite spot in DC, probably for all three of those reasons. Five stars.
Brilliant place, quiches were excellent followed by wonderful baklava and coffee. Owner was really welcoming and we will definitely be back to support this place during these uncertain times.
Delicious savory pastries and the owner was so nice and went the extra mile. A few outdoor tables on the street (temporary, due to COVID) to enjoy the food.
Wonderful home made Mediterranean food. Yum.
Lots of good food & very good service.
Small pastry shop up Wisconsin. Great selection and everything is wonderful!
Good service very delicious pastries nice place I like it
Nice place,yummy French pastry ,very friendly stuff
Delicious and Authentic!

Once a Dolcezza gelato shop is now a Mediterranean bakery. It's owned by the kindest couple. On a recent visit, they gave my toddler a free heart-shaped cookie. It's a small store with window seating only. However, since the pandemic, they added outdoor tables on the street. They sell baked goods, coffee and lunch items. My toddler enjoyed their chocolate croissant and my chicken souffle was filling and delicious!
So nice amazing food family owned 10/10 recommend
This place is perfect. You feel at home the moment you walk in. The chicken platter and merguez sandwich were delicious and a good price. We’ll be back for sure!
Delicious sandwiches, bakes, and sweets. Definitely worth checking out.
Breakfast food was great and the guy working in the shop was incredibly nice and genuine!
I woke up thinking about their house made Tzatiki. DELICIOUS!
Great Mediterranean food.

An absolute gem. Great place for gelato, pastry and coffee/expressive. Very nice decor and vibe. They soon are going to add food menu to their offering. A must try!!!.  We tried different gelato and there were all delicious, making it difficult to choose.
Cozy, excellent food, atmosphere. Felt like eating a home-cooked meal.
This place is a hidden gem. Everyone should try this and you WILL continue to go back. Authentic food, all of it is delicious.
Delicious fresh pastries. The man and wife who own the place are very friendly and lovely. Highly recommended!.
Perfect stop for a a great Americano and baklava!

If you like Hand-pies, Empanadas, Piroshki, etc. you will love their North-African/French version in a flaky dough, from the shores of the blue Mediterranean Sea. And the cookies/pastries are wonderful too!
Great homemade food
What a sweet and amazing experience! Staff was warm and friendly. They went above and beyond! Food was absolutely delicious! Definitely worth checking out!
Excellent place to enjoy relaxing time.  Disfrutar un cafecito es lo maximo. Please see photos for amenities interior of the place.
What a fantastic spot . Wonderful healthyish pastries, warm family owned and operated. You have to try the  Salep - a warm drink that will make your day.
Great people, great home made food
Stopped here on Christmas Day as I was vacationing by myself. The owner was so extraordinarily nice and the food, omg. Vegetarian Soufflé 💯💯💯. What a delightful experience.
Amazing family owned restaurant in the heart of Georgetown! Best almond croissant I've had in years. And so friendly, pretty decor, and tons of seating by the windows.

Delightful, cheerful, delicious! Loved the cappuccino and Kalb Al Louz- small square bar of semolina, honey, orange blossom water & ground almonds, with whole almond on top. Cosy tables and big sofa upstairs. Many savory options for meals, too.
Delicious fresh pastries in a beautiful little spot. The owners are very friendly and they make all of the food fresh themselves. We enjoyed are visit!

I absolutely loved this little cozy business! The food was some of the best I've had in years. The man and wife who run the business are very personal, respectful, and overall wonderful people. The building itself is easy to find, cozy and small, and perfectly clean. I can't say it enough the food was fresh, cooked fresh every morning, and was served quickly and kept warm and perfect. Can't recommend this place enough! If you get a chance come here!
We stopped in while exploring Georgetown, and we highly recommend it! The food is delicious and homemade!

Although it is certainly possible to get sandwiches and platters to take away, the food at La Jolie Bleue is delicious and beautifully cooked and far from the slapdash fare that so many smaller places offer.  This week I took away two dinner platters (one lamb, one vegetarian), a baguette and an almond croissant for the next day’s breakfast.  Both the dinner platters were flavorful, with a variety of roasted vegetables.  The lamb was exquisite, tender and falling off the bone.  The baguette was crusty and the almond croissant delicate with just the right amount of marizpan baked inside.  La Jolie Bleue is family owned and service is personal and warm, with explanations of how the dishes are made.  This restaurant is a gem and a wonderful addition to the neighborhood.
Great place to visit. Delicious bites and beautiful people making you feel welcomed.
We love the foods here. Not only foods, but also the service and street view. Highly recommend 😋
Owner is a lovely man, the pastries are homemade and the real deal! Support local businesses 😊
Great homemade pastries and sweets, excellent service very friendly family-owned business

Sooo happy to have discovered this little gem!! The kofta (ground beef and lamb) pastry with lentil soup were absolutely delicious. And don’t get me started on the desserts; favorites were the Napoleon and Qalb Looz. Also it’s family owned, and their welcoming hospitality is truly what sets it apart. Can’t wait to visit again soon!
Amazing fresh croissants and pastries!
Wonderful spot that's has delicious Mediterranean and algerian meals and delicacies. And very nice owner and staff!
Excellent food. Everything is prepared from SCRATCH! I highly recommend the souffles and the sweets.
Amazing vibes, great family owned bakery with superb sorbetto!
Best breakfast in town.
Excellent
Fabulous food and the owners are so sweet and generous, very cute dining area upstairs, you need to try this place.
Spectacular and expanding Mediterranean food choices, cooked and sold by friendly and devoted owners.

This is my new favorite place in Georgetown! The food/drinks is amazing, the staff are incredibly friendly and generous, and they will give you samples when they have them! But really, I love the food here (also try the green drink!). We will 100% be back!
The food here was amazing and everything was freshly baked. Also the fruit refresher is really good. Probably the best smoothie I’ve had. Owners are very nice and friendly. 👌
Great family owned bakery. Good for a quick bite
A great selection  of fresh Mediterranean food. Everything is delicious from pastries to salty items. It is a family business. The owners are kind and welcoming. I highly recommend la Jolie Bleue!

Great place! My wife and I came late Sunday night and were treated like family. The owner Tahir and his son provided great service and food itself was outstanding. We had both chicken and lamb soufflés and pistachio and strawberry gelato . Highly recommend and we will be definitely visiting when we are back in Georgetown.
Cozy family owned spot with good drinks and middle eastern and French pastries

La Jolie Bleue is an absolutely terrific little restaurant with delicious healthy Mediterranean food, pastries, smoothies, gelato and espresso. The food is so delicious and reasonably priced and the husband and wife owners are so lovely and warm. I recommend it wholeheartedly.
Delicious Gelato! Will be back to try other things!
Excellent pastries and fresh juices. A very warm and friendly staff too.
The pastries are absolutely magnificent! They are light & airy yet flavorful & filling. The service... you'll feel like you have an invited special guest in someones home. Love this place!
La Jolie Bleue is my new favorite bakery in Georgetown -- all the pastries are fresh and delicious and everyone who works here is friendly and helpful.
Incredible ambience and even better staff! Nothing better than fresh food with all the ingredients known🙏😁
What a great find! Tahar & his wife make beautiful & delicious food & drinks...thank you for the hospitality. Love this little place!
Great, quiet little cafe on Wisconsin Avenue. The most chilled out one in all of DC, and a nice addition to the neighbourhood :) I love it.
Amazing pastries and a great place to do work! Free WiFi.
Great oriental pastries.  Will transport you to North Africa in a mouthful!

La Jolie Bleue is absolutely fantastic! The pastries (both savory and sweet) are to die for and the service is absolutely wonderful. The owners appear to be very proud of their new café and they should be. Its absolutely delightful - make sure you try the baklava with real honey!

This is an AMAZING addition to Georgetown. Delicious delicacies in a tastily decorated and relaxed setting. The drinks, the French pastries  do not easily leave your taste buds once you eat. Words cannot express the refined and freshly baked products. It’s a must for family and friends. Mohamed Muhsin Potomac
Delicious coffee, sweets, Fresh Fruit Juice, and Savories

This family-owned café is very cute and cozy! The pastries melt in your mouth and the drinks are so refreshing! I especially recommend the mille-feuille pastry, chicken soufflé, and fruit refresher drink. Everyone is very friendly and welcoming and the food all tastes very fresh and homemade! I’d 10/10 recommend coming here, very enjoyable :)
Great service! The ambiance is very warm and welcoming. A great place to bring family.

Yummie veggie and meat pastries and desserts, made fresh daily, plus refreshing smoothies and coffee (I had an Americano.)  The upstairs has tables and chairs and is a great space to settle in and work (free wifi).  It's fun to support these father and son owners in their new cafe.  They have been selling their food at the farmers market for many years.
